pgTitle: List of programmes broadcast by TVNZ

rows.text: Rural New Zealand show where South Island farmers compete against North Island farmers to round up sheep with their dog only using a dog whistle. The winner received a trophy, show presented by John Gordon.
Sports Quiz show where two teams of New Zealand sporting personalities competed against each other. The winning team each week had the choice of charity to donate prize money to.
Are You Smarter Than a 10 Year Old?
Political talk show. Ended when TVNZ 7 was closed down in 2012. Picked up by Prime in 2013.
Toddler show featuring Bumble the Bee and his friends
Weekly current affairs show screened Thursday nights on TV1 this show has no connection to the show of the same name that screened weeknights on TV1 between 2004 and 2012.
Period soap which succeeded Close to Home.
Eye to Eye with Willie Jackson
Comedy show that made fun of current events, politics and anything else on New Zealand television using characters dressed with sculpted face to resemble a various politicians and TV stars.
Current affairs show featuring overseas stories presented by TVNZ Foreign Correspondents.
School holiday replacement, screened in place of After School during school holidays.
News and current affairs show screened Sunday nights on TV1.
Reality show hunting famous New Zealand ghosts
Scott Hunter tries to track down his father in New Zealand's gold-prospecting country in 1860.
New Zealands worst reality show where a group of people were placed in a house and had to survive with nothing but an Internet connected computer.
Reality/travel show where celebrities travel to foreign countries and do "as the Romans do"
Drama series set in the fictional town of Jackson's Wharf
The successor to New Zealand's Funniest Home Videos.
Jointly made Australian–New Zealand drama series. Cancelled after one season
Reality show following the trials of people getting their driver licenses.
Licensed version of Joe Schmo. A reality TV show featuring several actors pretending to be contestants in a game show and one man who thinks it's all real.
Reality show where the DIY Rescue team repair unfinished DIY work done to a home or DIY work that has gone wrong.
Show that gave an open home tour of peoples homes, the homes were usually luxury homes. The show usually featured a celebritys home as well.
Palmers Garden Show / Maggies Garden Show
Reality show seeing if couples who want children can raise someone else's children for a week.
Cooking show where two teams of celebrities compete to cook the best meal in a certain time.
Reality television show about delinquent children; Season 1 ended April 2006
Longest-running queer issues show in the world.
Dramas in a family-owned trucking firm.
Reality television show where celebrities are surprised and put through the wringer.
So You Wanna Be a Popstar?
Original run 2003–2005 on TV2 and returned to air in 2008.
Youth related news and entertainment show.

Regional news show screened exclusively in the lower North Island (and originally the Upper South Island), broadcast from TVNZ studios in Wellington. Originally screened during a time period where each region screened a regional news show during the Network news, later moved to before the Network news.

Magazine style show, presenters traveled around towns in New Zealand interviewing the locals and talking about issues in the region. As this show featured before TVNZ programming was networked each area of the country hads its own local version.
The Bugs Bunny Show The Cartoon Company

Regional news show screened exclusively in the upper South Island broadcast from TVNZ studios in Christchurch. Originally screened during a time period where each region screened a regional news show during the Network news, later moved to before the Network news.
Magazine show aimed at gays and lesbians. Ran for a trial ten episodes as a possible QueerNation replacement.
Reality show putting famous New Zealanders back into school with their younger "clone" version of themselves.
Reality show where two contestants must swap occupations for a day.
Reality television show; Survivor-like, only mainly with celebrities.
One hour news bulletin screened at 8pm.
5 minute news bulletin screened on the hour each hour.
Late night version of U Live, this version featured less music and more talk.
Daily presenter based entertainment show featuring movie, music reviews and interviews. Ended when TVNZ U went off the air on 31st August 2013.
Quiz show between teams of students representing Universities around in New Zealand
Presented by Jayne Kieley this reality series followed a couples wedding and preparation for the wedding.
